caption: b"Looking for a binge-worthy show to watch right now? We might be biased but you'll want to see what all of the hype is about in the Netflix-original drama, @thecrownnetflix. Spoiler alert: you'll spot this vintage #Cummins racing jacket, but we won\xe2\x80\x99t reveal what episode! :crown:"

b'A tried-and-true vessel that is equally functional and durable. :check_mark: 

This modern steel cargo ship is dedicated to carrying feed to the Shetland Island Salmon farms along the coast of Scotland, leaving room for only three crew members. Swipe :backhand_index_pointing_right: for a look inside the engine room to find three six-cylinder Cummins KTA19 engines. 

#Cummins #CumminsMarine #MarineMonday'

b"How do you build an engine that will run for over 1 million miles? Well that's easy, thanks to our employees at the Columbus Mid-Range Engine Plant. Get a behind-the-scenes look at how we redefine what a truck can do :backhand_index_pointing_up: \n\n#Cummins #RamTrucks"

b"#MarineMonday or fighting fires? :fire: Either way, thank the @sffdpio. Powered by three Cummins QSK19-M Tier III engines, the St. Francis fire boat has the capacity to pump over 18,000 gallons of water per minute. We're proud to power products that support the safety of our communities in every corner of the world. #Cummins"
b'Hi, there. :waving_hand: We\xe2\x80\x99re the 101-year old company that has something to say about Hydrogen. \n\nLearn more at the link in our bio! #Cummins #GenerationH #Hydrogen'

b'If Hydrogen was your best friend in high school, it would totally be named \xe2\x80\x9cMost likely to lead the world to a carbon-free future.\xe2\x80\x9d Talk about a glow up. We\xe2\x80\x99re taking #hydrogen out of the chemistry lab and into the spotlight during our virtual Hydrogen Day event. Register now at the link in bio! #Cummins #GenerationH'

b'Educating marine students is a tall task, but @callofthesea does just that. A @Cummins hybrid tall ship, the brigantine Matthew Turner, which operates on a carbon-neutral basis is used to educate the next generation of sailors. The vessel is made of and powered by materials and methods that meet the highest sustainability and recycling standards. Learn more at the link in bio! \n\n#MarineMonday #Cummins #CumminsMarine'

b'This or that? Turns or straightaways? How well do you think you know @clintbowyer? Before retiring from #NASCAR after the 2020 season, we asked Clint 21 questions to learn more about his favorite things! \n\n#SHRacing #Cummins  @stewarthaasracing'

b"Here's to 93 years of blue jackets and gold standards! @Cummins is proud to support the 93rd annual, and for this year virtual, edition of the 2020 @NationalFFA convention. Will you be attending? Comment with :raised_hand: below!  #Cummins #FFA20 #Agriculture #FarmLife #Farming"

b"Going the extra mile each and every day, we're thankful for truck drivers like Michael and Jack. From delivering life's necessities to fueling the economy, we're committed to keeping truckers on the move. Hear what they love about their jobs! \n\n#Cummins #ThankATrucker"

b'Clear your plate! :fork_and_knife_with_plate_selector: The Baan Khanitha Cruise is a fully equipped floating restaurant along the Chao Phraya river in Thailand. This ultimate dining experience is all powered by a Cummins 4BTA 3.9-liter generator, providing ample power for the kitchen, lighting and entertainment systems. 

We want to see your Cummins powered vessels! Tag us @Cummins and use #MarineMonday for your chance to be featured. 

#Cummins #CumminsMarine #floatingrestaurant'

b"What are the key ingredients for helping farmers increase fuel efficiency and save money? Learn more by watching part two of our farmer's guide to get the most out of your Cummins powered equipment. :tractor: \n\n#Cummins #farming #agriculture #fueltips"

b"Meet Red Sky! A 100' @nautorswan_official underwent a major refit at @lyman_morse during the winter season to be repowered with a Cummins QSB6.7 305hp light duty commercial engine. It's no wonder the owner and Captains are loving the vessel's finishing touches! :water_wave: 
 
Tag us @Cummins and use #MarineMonday for your chance to be featured on an upcoming post. 

#CumminsMarine #NautorSwan #refit"

b'As a proud partner for over 15 years, Cummins is excited to work with @inblackexpoinc in their commitment to the betterment of the communities around us for over 50 years. Be sure to join alongside our employees in the (free, yes free!) virtual Minority Small Business and IBX Series running throughout October. More details here: https://www.indianablackexpo.com/'

b"Don't try this at home! This 47-foot United States Coast Guard (USCG) motor lifeboat proves the our new QSC8.3-530hp engines can do just about anything! During a roll-over test, the engines remained running while doing a complete 360 in the water. This is the very first of 117 more boats to be powered by Cummins. 

Who's been out on the water? Tag us @Cummins and use #MarineMonday for your chance to be featured! 

#CumminsMarine #MarineMonday #USCG #coastguard #lifeboat"

b"We're honoring the hard work of farmers everywhere in celebration of National Farmer's Day. Be sure to check out these tips to increase your fuel efficiency, so you can remain focused on feeding the world. Thank you, farmers! \n\n#NationalFarmersDay #Cummins"

b'Something old, something new, something borrowed, something on the bay... Once a one of a kind self-propelled wedding chapel, Chapel on the Bay has seen more than 1,000 "I do's"! What's not to love with twin 115hp Cummins diesels giving the 33 ton vessel top speeds? 

Share your @Cummins powered boat by tagging us and using #MarineMonday. 

#Cummins #CumminsMarine #houseboat #boating'

b'This year marks the eighth anniversary of Manufacturing Day, and amid the COVID-19 pandemic, historic unemployment and majority opportunity gaps, this might be the most important one yet. Today, we\'re asking our followers to help us thank our talented and dedicated manufacturing and supply chain employees for their tireless work and dedication in what can only be described as an extraordinary year. To those on the frontlines who are helping keep the economy operational and our communities safe, we say "thank you." :red_heart_selector:'

b"How much time do you spend listening to podcasts? To celebrate #InternationalPodcastDay :studio_microphone_selector: we're excited to announce our new podcast: Brightest Bulbs. Now, you can expand your knowledge of energy and power technologies by subscribing at the link in our bio!\n\n#Energy #Podcast #Cummins"

b'At Cummins, our data center specialists keep your Confidence On. Our large network of experts protect you from uncertainty. As a top global provider of backup power solutions for the data center industry, our team works where your data lives. \n\n#ConfidenceOn #Cloud #BigData #Connectivity #Cummins'

b"Need a cure for the Monday blues? Look no further than this baby boat! The Boomin Beaver was originally built to herd logs in waterways, but don't underestimate it's ability to tow small ships and even deploy underwater security fences. Can you guess what engine powers this tugboat? 

Use #MarineMonday to share your @Cummins powered boat. 

#Cummins #CumminsMarine #tugboat"

b"For a century, Cummins has driven the innovation that powers the world. Today, we're creating energy solutions to power a better future. Welcome to the next generation of power! #CumminsPowerGen100"

b"The Water-Go-Round Ferry will be making a splash as the first fuel cell vessel in the U.S. and the first commercial fuel cell ferry in the world. Operating in the San Francisco Bay, this 84 passenger e-ferry will be powered by 360kW of Hydrogenics' fuel cell power modules - the only byproduct of propelling this boat is water!

Learn more about Cummins\xe2\x80\x99 commitment to innovation and the future of hydrogen-powered ferries in an upcoming virtual webinar at the link in our bio. Don't forget to tag us with your @Cummins vessel photos using #MarineMonday

#Cummins #CumminsMarine #Hydrogen #FuelCells #HydrogenPropulsion #Sustainability #Webinar"

b"Did you know trucks haul more than $10.4 trillion worth of merchandise each year? Ahead of National Truck Driver Appreciation Week, it's the perfect time to give thanks to the 3.5 million professional drivers by being courteous on the road. \n\n#ThankATrucker #Cummins"

b"Over the last few weeks we've highlighted several Cummins employees and customers who have gone out of their way to help those in their communities during the #COVID19 pandemic. So today, meet Stephen, a Cummins employee in the UK who used his past experience as a medical gas quality controller to volunteer and test the medical gases used in ventilators at two new emergency hospitals being built in London. Watch to learn how Stephen came through for his community in a major way, and check out five similar stories that will leave you feeling equally inspired by clicking the link in our bio. #LifeAtCummins"

b'Cummins employees around the world continue building innovative products during this challenging time. We\xe2\x80\x99re proud to serve customers like Ryn, who depend on us to keep their family business going. That \xe2\x80\x9cC\xe2\x80\x9d on the fender is something you can always count on. #Cummins #RAM #LaborDay'

b"When you're responsible for delivering time sensitive cargo and passengers on the open seas, sometimes you need an extra dose of power and innovation that typical crew boats don't contain. The Cummins-powered Seacor Panther finds that extra power and innovation in the form of four 95-liter engines and three Cummins QSM11 generators. Learn more at the link in bio!

Have an interesting Cummins marine story to share? Tag us @Cummins and use #MarineMonday to feature your vessel!

#Cummins #CumminsMarine #Seacor #QSK95 #Catamaran (Photo courtesy of SEACOR)"

b'You know what day it is... #MarineMonday! A Maine fishing boat, the 32 Holland, is the first of its kind to host a 550hp Cummins engine. This hull can house a 6TBA, QSB5.9 or, in this case, a QSB6.7. With this level of power and a top speed of 35.5 knots, our products are a premier fit for this vessel.

Like what you see? Tag us @cummins and use #CumminsMarine to share your experience for a chance to be featured.

#Cummins #CumminsMarine #tunafishing #boating #Maine #Holland'

b"You might recognize this Harbor Harvest vessel and its work to help the local community, but do you know how it operates? For this week's #MarineMonday feature we're bringing you a one-of-a-kind hybrid catamaran vessel. Not only does this boat serve local farmers by delivering their home-grown goods to the Big Apple, but it completes its trips in the most sustainable way. Read more about how long a voyage for Harbor Harvest compared to their highway counterparts takes to complete at the link in our bio. 
 
Share your Cummins powered vessel with us by tagging us @cummins and using #MarineMonday.
 
#Cummins #CumminsMarine #FarmToTable #EatLocal #Hybrid #Sustainability"

b"There are countless examples of Cummins employees stepping up during #COVID19. Using his background in economics and computer science, Stephen was able to create a model to better predict the spread of the virus in the Columbus, Indiana community. Check out the video above, and learn more about Stephen's story by clicking the link in our bio."

b'The @fv_seahound brings "work hard, play hard" to life. This family-owned 37-foot lobster boat based out of Hampton, New Hampshire (USA) carries up to 800 traps on the weekends. In it's free time, you'll find the boat on sunset cruises and other fun excursions. Read more at the link in our bio. 
 
We want to see your Cummins powered boats! Tag us @cummins and use #MarineMonday in your posts. 
 
#Cummins #CumminsMarine #LobsterBoat #lobstering #fishing #commericalfishing #lobsta #seatotable #offshorefishing #downeastboat #fishingboat #newengland'

b'For Cummins customer @HarborHarvest, a typical work week involves sustainably transporting food from farm to harbor to your table. But since the start of COVID-19, the Norwalk, Connecticut-based business has helped the local community by using their resources to donate PPE and hand sanitizer produced by local craft distilleries to those who need it most. Learn how Harbor Harvest and other Cummins customers are stepping up to help local communities by clicking the link in our bio.'

b"A Cummins QSK95 series engine could produce as much horsepower as 25 passenger cars combined. When used in a power generator, a single unit could power over 1,500 homes.\n\nSo, how do you build one of the world's largest diesel engines? Watch how our employees in Seymour, IN (USA) are safely manufacturing the QSK95 during the pandemic."

b"We're proud to partner with customers like Atlantic Coast Energy Group. Providing emergency fueling services to New York City-area hospitals is no small order. With their fleet of trucks powered by Cummins natural gas engines, Atlantic Coast Energy Group is carrying out a truly life-saving service during #COVID19. Watch the video and click the link in our bio to learn more."

b"Rising to the occasion and helping communities during times of need. It's what Cummins customers like @SunCoastResources are doing during the #COVID19 pandemic. View Sun Coast's story :backhand_index_pointing_up:  and learn more by clicking the link in our bio."

b"Start your engines... Cummins has set the pace for innovation and there's no stopping us! It\xe2\x80\x99s a historic Fourth of July filled with @NASCAR and @indycar all weekend long at the @Indianapolismotorspeedway. Who are you excited to watch on @nbcsports? :chequered_flag:\n\n#INDYGP #BackyardBrickyard"

b"Happy First Day of Summer! :smiling_face_with_sunglasses::water_wave: If you're spending time on the water, comment below or use #CumminsMarine to share a photo of your Cummins powered boat! No matter what activity you have planned, be sure to read 5 safety tips at the link in bio.\n\n#Cummins #Boating #Fishing"

b'Did you know 800 power generators combined, weigh as much as 3,000 forest elephants? Cummins is shipping 8,000 tons of engines to ensure our lives stay connected, as many countries are slowly opening back up. Read more at the link in bio!\n\n#energy #Cummins #datacenters'

b'If you close your eyes, you can almost hear @PurdueBands lead 350K race fans through "Back Home Again." Today has us dreaming about the moonlight on the Wabash and the safe return to racing @IndianapolisMotorSpeedway. #500AtHome #Indy500 #Cummins'

b'On #InternationalFirefightersDay we thank all of the brave individuals who risk their lives to protect our communities. Being a firefighter demands many personal sacrifices and we celebrate your courage and commitment to protect us. #ThankAFirefighter'

b'We count on truck drivers to help keep shelves stocked, hospitals supplied and first responders equipped. Thanks to all of the truckers on the road who continue to deliver around the clock. Whoever it may be, help us #ThankATrucker by tagging them in the comments below! You can also share a photo of the truck driver in your life to your Instagram account and tag us @Cummins. We may just regram your post!'

b'To help respond to the #COVID19 pandemic we\xe2\x80\x99ve announced additional efforts to help protect the needs of health care professionals. We will manufacture high efficiency particulate filters for use in @3m Powered Air Purifying Respirators (PAPRs). Read the latest at the link in our bio. (PAPR photo credit: 3M)'

b'We are proud to partner with DuPont to use our filter technology to supply critical material that will help address the nation\xe2\x80\x99s shortage of N95 respirator masks. The first mask prototypes using Cummins\xe2\x80\x99 donated media were assembled by @umntwincities teams to provide masks to @mhealthfairview and other Minneapolis-based healthcare systems. Click the link in our bio to read the full story. #Cummins #COVID19'

b'Maybe it\xe2\x80\x99s because we\xe2\x80\x99ve been serving the agriculture industry for over 100 years, but we think every day should be National Agriculture Day. If you can\xe2\x80\x99t live without your morning coffee you aren\xe2\x80\x99t alone. Did you know that worldwide, we drink approximately 2 billion cups of coffee every day? The coffee that we drink is cultivated by hardworking growers powered by machines like this \xe2\x80\x93 the @oxbointernational 9240 coffee harvester, featuring a Cummins Tier 3 F2.8 engine. Here\xe2\x80\x99s to all of you coffee growers (and drinkers) out there. :hot_beverage: Swipe left to see the Cummins engine under the hood. \n#NationalAgWeek2020 #nationalagday #aglife #farmlife #cummins'

b"Have you thanked a truck driver lately? According to the American Trucking Association there are more than 3.5 million truck drivers...and that's just in the United States! We thank all the truck drivers who are working around the clock and around the world to deliver critical supplies and materials. We're grateful for the world's truck drivers today and every day, for all you do."

b"Did you know: Over 90% of farms globally are run by an individual or a family, and family farms occupy a large majority of the world\xe2\x80\x99s agricultural land, producing approximately 80% of the world\xe2\x80\x99s food. Family farming is more important than ever, and we're proud to support farmers and other agriculture professionals around the world. Here's how Andy, one of our Machine Integration Lead Engineers, discovered Cummins power on his family farm. :tractor: #Cummins #agday20 #agriculture #farming"

b'Think about it: Every meal we eat is provided by the world\xe2\x80\x99s farming community. During National Agriculture Week, we want to recognize the 28% of the world\xe2\x80\x99s population who work to bring our food to the table. Thank you to all farmers out there, big and small for all you do. Join us in celebrating the agriculture community by thanking your farmer friends in the comments below. :tractor: :ear_of_corn: #Cummins #AgDay20 #Agriculture #Farming'

b'Our latest Cummins-powered Machine of the Month is dedicated to tugboats. These relatively small but mighty vessels have an awfully big job: Helping massive cargo ships - which can take up to 5 miles to stop - maneuver in tight quarters and dock. \nWhen the Ghana Ports and Harbor Authority needed new tugboats, they called on the world-class design of @robertallanltd, the ship-building expertise of the Tor Group and the reliable power of Cummins. Powered by two Cummins QSK95 marine engines with 3,600 BHP each, the tugboats have the necessary power needed to maneuver massive cargo ships around the Takoradi Harbour.  For more information on the tugboats, visit the link in the bio. :ferry: :camera_with_flash: credit: Tor Group \n#cummins #tugboat #tugboats  #maritime'

b'Cummins celebrates @internationalwomensday_global and the two-year anniversary of Cummins Powers Women. The program focuses on the advancement and prosperity of girls and women around the world. Since then, more than 100,000 people have been served and counting. Join us by clicking the link in our bio to learn more. #IWD2020 #EachforEqual #CumminsPowersWomen'

b'As Engineers Week 2020 comes to an end, shout out to all of the engineers here @Cummins for their endless creativity and ingenuity. Is there an engineer who inspires you? Show your support by thanking them in the comments below! #Eweek2020 #Cummins #LifeAtCummins'

b'As Engineers Week 2020 comes to an end, shout out to all of the engineers here @Cummins for their endless creativity and ingenuity. Is there an engineer who inspires you? Show your support by thanking them in the comments below! #Eweek2020 #Cummins #LifeAtCummins'

b'Through the Cummins Powers Women program, Cummins employees have the unique opportunity to advocate equality for women and girls around the globe. From discussions on resilience and vulnerability, to meeting with @GovHolcomb at the Indiana Statehouse, here\xe2\x80\x99s to the more than 35 girls from five different @GirlsInc chapters who joined Cummins leaders this week to learn about the power of advocacy. #Cummins #LifeAtCummins #CumminsPowersWomen #GirlDay2020 #Advocacy'

b'From the farm to the field to the future, @cummins has powered the agriculture industry for over 100 years. At the 2020 World Ag Expo, you can find over 20 applications powered by Cummins and catch a first-hand glimpse of the new structural 4-cylinder engine, which is making its North American debut. The new Cummins F3.8/F4.5 structural product provides a compact and capable four-cylinder option for tractors in the 90-200hp powerband. Couldn\xe2\x80\x99t make it to World Ag? Not a problem. Click the link in our bio to learn more. :ear_of_corn: :sheaf_of_rice: #Cummins #worldagexpo #worldagexpo2020 #agriculture'
